Feed post

Yash PratapYash Pratap • YouVerified • You Web Dev, System Design, AIWeb Dev, System Design, AI 2w • Edited • 2 weeks ago • Edited • Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn
If you are a rich Indian and felt suffocated on LinkedIn India as now it is captured by the middle class of Urban India, then hashtag#Substack is really great for you.

Culture of practice is always defined by the rich people.

When you say, “Hey, this person is hashtag#cringe“ then what you actually meant is these people don’t have the similar cultural contexts as the elites.

In India, Cultural contexts of elites are mostly hashtag#covertly_patriarchal with a higher baseline where people are more civilized in comparison.

Elites value individual freedom, especially for women, because their previous generations of women already fought religion and its norms on their behalf.

Most people say rich people, especially rich women, are fake, but in reality they are just searching for inclusivity, which they are not able to find in highly unequal society.

Solution doesn’t exists in hashtag#whitewashing the privilege like Sudha Murthy saying “Hey I am middle class, I am middle class” or staying away from middle class or poor like a feudal lord or lady but in acknowledgement of privilege.

You can solve this by migrating to western countries to a certain level because their ancestors paid the price—and in extreme cases, death—for questioning the orthodox church but they haven’t made it inclusive for Indians because there are no incentives for West to learn Indian culture and racism isn’t dead yet.

Indian elites never question orthodoxy religion properly.

In fact, in most cases, their absurd level of unearned privilege comes from religion, caste, and class, so questioning orthodox religion means questioning their own privilege.

That’s why Indian Urban Elite feminism doesn’t include lower-class and low-caste women or minority women.

That’s why Indian Urban Elite feminism excludes Dr. Ambedkar, Jyotiba and Savitri Phule, but it also excludes mainstream feminists who gave the idea of feminism itself, like Virginia Woolf and Simone and if you read Simone de Beauvoir, you will find her calling women golddiggers in lighter terms and discussing how golddigging leads to the loss of identity.

When Indian Urban Elite feminists strip away the core intellectuals, then it becomes some weird form of low IQ activism which older men took lightly, like a joke.

Fighting orthodoxy religion is not “Hey orthodoxy religion is bad, Hey orthodoxy religion is bad” but discarding the “orthodoxy” aspects of the religion and this is not a low-IQ job which can be done by activism simply.

It requires lots of creativity and wisdom.

Instead of saying “Patriarchy is Bad”, “Patriarchy is Bad”

Virginia Woolf invented the method of stream of consciousness where she took you inside the psyche of the character.

One of her brilliant work Orlando where she changed the gender of person across centuries and make people see how life looks differently for women and men without any exaggeration and it bring more long term sustainable change than any normal activism and that’s Genius.
